# [IABOPEN](../wg/iabopen.html)

## Summary

The IABOPEN session at IETF 126 was chaired by Dhruv Dhody (IAB Chair) and Yaroslav Rosomakho (IAB Member). The session featured updates on the IAB document status, technical liaison activities with IEEE 802.1, proposed updates to the IAB's liaison process documents, global outreach efforts, and the technical draft on protocol greasing. The session concluded with an invited talk by Luis Biltsing from the Austrian Chamber of Labor on the regulatory and technical challenges of protecting minors on social media platforms.

---

## Key Discussion Points

### 1. Welcome and Status Update
Dhruv Dhody and Yaroslav Rosomakho opened the meeting with a status update on IAB activities and publications, using the slide deck [1_Welcome and Status Update](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-iabopen-1-welcome-and-status-update-00).

* **Document Status:** The IAB recently published three workshop report RFCs. The IPGO workshop report has been approved and will soon be sent to the RFC Editor. Two liaison management documents and the protocol greasing draft are currently active on the IAB stream.
* **Liaison Statements & Appeals:** The IAB responded to an ITU-T TSB liaison regarding E.164 country codes and `e164.arpa`. Responses to ITU-T SG17 are pending. The IAB received and responded to three appeals since the last IETF meeting.
* **New Work Shepherding:** A New Work Help Desk was held on Monday, with another scheduled for Thursday, to help community members navigate the process of introducing new work to the IETF.

