### 2. Liaison Update: IEEE 802.1
Janos Farkas presented an update on coordination activities with the IEEE 802.1 working group, based on [2_Liaison Update: IEEE 802.1](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-iabopen-1-liaison-update-ieee-8021-02).

* **Coordination Framework:** The joint coordination effort is led by Russ Housley (IETF) and Robert Stacy (IEEE 802). The team coordinates active items via virtual meetings and collocated workshops, such as the joint session in Madrid.
* **TSN and DETNET Alignment (Item 25):** The IEEE 802.1 Time-Sensitive Networking (TSN) Task Group (focusing on Layer 2) and the IETF Deterministic Networking (DETNET) Working Group (focusing on Layer 3) coordinate to deliver end-to-end deterministic connectivity. DETNET leverages TSN as a primary subnet technology.
* **Active Technical Items:**
  * **YANG Modules:** Ongoing efforts to develop YANG modules for new IEEE 802.1 standards.
  * **802.1DC (Quality of Service):** Standardizes QoS techniques for non-bridge systems like routers and firewalls (primarily triggered by DETNET requirements).
  * **LLDPv2:** Triggered by the Link State Vector Routing (LSVR) group to support multi-frame LLDP.
  * **Security:** Ongoing coordination on post-quantum cryptography.

